<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-08T11:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-08T11:40:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1700.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-08T12:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1915—noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Jiménes informed me today that Government anticipates several
                            small disturbances as forerunner of revolution. He added that steps are
                            being taken to apprehend leaders and arrests will be made today.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>